{"title_page": "List of California Golden Bears bowl games", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:Robert Jordan gets tackled AFB 071231-F-0558K-015.JPEG|thumb|alt=An American football player in a blue jersey tackles a player in a white jersey on a football field.|250px|On offense during the [[2007 Armed Forces Bowl]].]]\nThe [[California Golden Bears]] [[college football]] [[California Golden Bears football|team]] competes as part of the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] (NCAA) Division I [[Football Bowl Subdivision]] (FBS), representing the [[University of California, Berkeley]] in the North Division of the [[Pac-12 Conference]] (Pac-12). Since the establishment of the team in 1886, California has appeared in 24 [[bowl game]]s,<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://calbears.com/documents/2019/7/24/2019_Cal_Football_Record_Book.pdf|title=2019 California Football Record Book|work=Cal Athletics|publisher=University of California, Berkeley|accessdate=December 28, 2019}}</ref> including eight appearances in the [[Rose Bowl Game]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> Their latest bowl appearance was the [[2019 Redbox Bowl]], where California won against the [[2019 Illinois Fighting Illini football team|Illinois Fighting Illini]] 35\u201320,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/sports/article/Cal-captures-first-bowl-win-since-2015-beating-14940402.php|title=Cal beats Illinois in Redbox Bowl, first bowl win since 2015|author=Rusty Simmons|publisher=SF Chronicle|date=December 30, 2019|accessdate=December 30, 2019}}</ref> to give the Golden Bears an overall bowl record of 12\u201311\u20131 (.521).\n\n==Key==\n<center>{{Col-begin|width=50%}}\n{{Col-break}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+General\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#e3e3e3;\"| {{dagger}}\n| Bowl game record attendance \n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#d0e7ff;\"| {{double-dagger}}\n| Former bowl game record attendance \n|}\n{{Col-break}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Results\n|-\n| style=\"background:#dfd;\"| W\n| Win\n|-\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| L\n| Loss\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffffe6;\"| T\n| Tie\n|}\n{{Col-break}}\n{{col-end}}</center>\n\n==Bowl games==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ List of bowl games showing bowl played in, score, date, season, opponent, stadium, location, attendance and head coach{{#tag:ref|Statistics correct as of [[2019\u201320 NCAA football bowl games]].|group=\"A\"}}\n! scope=\"col\" |#\n! scope=\"col\" |Bowl\n! scope=\"col\" |Score{{#tag:ref|Results are sortable first by whether the result was a California win, loss or tie and then second by the [[margin of victory]].|group=\"A\"}}\n! scope=\"col\" |Date\n! scope=\"col\" |Season{{#tag:ref|Links to the season article for the California team that competed in the bowl for that year.|group=\"A\"}}\n! scope=\"col\" |Opponent{{#tag:ref|Links to the season article for the opponent that California competed against in the bowl for that year when available or to their general page when unavailable.|group=\"A\"}}\n! scope=\"col\" |Stadium\n! scope=\"col\" |Location\n! scope=\"col\" |Attendance<ref name=\"NCAAAtt\">Bowl/All-Star Game Records, pp. 32\u201338</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" |Head coach\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|1\n! scope=\"row\" |[[1921 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]]\n|style=\"background:#dfd;\"|{{sort|W 28|W 28\u20130}}\n|{{dts|1921|01|01}}\n|[[1920 California Golden Bears football team|1920]]\n|[[1920 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|Ohio State Buckeyes]]\n|[[Tournament Park]]\n|[[Pasadena, California|Pasadena]]\n|style=\"background:#d0e7ff;\"|{{sort|042,000|42,000}}<sup>{{double-dagger}}</sup>\n|{{Sortname|Andy|Smith|Andy Smith (American football)}}\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2\n! scope=\"row\" |[[1922 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]]\n|style=\"background:#ffffe6;\"|{{sort|T 00|T 0\u20130}}\n|{{dts|1922|01|02}}\n|[[1921 California Golden Bears football team|1921]]\n|[[1921 Washington & Jefferson Presidents football team|Washington & Jefferson Presidents]