ards EnsembleTVComedy 2000\u20132009}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shum, Harry Jr.}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male actors of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:American dancers of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from San Francisco]]\n[[Category:American choreographers]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American people of Cantonese descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Hong Kong descent]]\n[[Category:American hip hop dancers]]\n[[Category:American musicians of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Costa Rican emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Musicians from the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:People from Lim\u00f3n Province]]\n[[Category:Costa Rican people of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Costa Rican people of Hong Kong descent]]\n[[Category:San Francisco State University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| image              = Harry Shum Jr. podczas San Diego ComicCon 2017.jpg\n| caption            = Shum at the [[San Diego Comic-Con]] in July 2017\n| name               = Harry Shum Jr.\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1982|4|28}}\n| birth_place        = [[Lim\u00f3n, Costa Rica]]\n| occupation         = {{Flat list|\n[[Dance]]r<br>[[Choreography|Choreographer]]<br>[[Actor]]<br>[[Singing|Singer]]\n}}\n| years_active       = 2000s\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Shelby Rabara]]|November 22, 2015}}\n| children           = 1\n| website            = {{url|http://www.harryshumjr.com/}}\n| module             = {{Infobox Chinese\n |child=yes\n |c={{linktext|lang=zh|\u5c91|\u52c7|\u5eb7}}\n |y=S\u00e0hm Y\u00fahngh\u014dng\n |j=sam4 jung5 hong1\n |p=C\u00e9n Y\u01d2ngk\u0101ng\n }}\n| signature          = Harry Shum Jr Signature.png\n}}\n\n'''Harry Shum Jr.''' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: \u5c91\u52c7\u5eb7<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/HarryShumJr/status/20090690334|title=\u5c91\u52c7\u5eb7 woah!!! My first Chinese tweet!  Lol. That's my Chinese name.  Wish I knew how to write more...|last=Jr|first=Harry Shum|date=2010-08-01|website=@HarryShumJr|language=en|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>; [[Cantonese Yale]]: ''S\u00e0hm Y\u00fahngh\u014dng''; born April 28, 1982) is a Chinese-American actor, singer, dancer, and choreographer. He is best known for his roles as [[Mike Chang]] on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] television series ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' (2009\u20132015), and as [[List of The Mortal Instruments characters#Magnus Bane|Magnus Bane]] on the [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] television series ''[[Shadowhunters]]'' (2016\u20132019). He was nominated for four [[Screen Actors Guild Awards]] for his performance in ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'', winning once and he won the award for The Male TV Star of 2018 in the [[E! People's Choice Awards]] for ''[[Shadowhunters]]''.\n\nHe has appeared in the films ''[[Step Up 2: The Streets]]'' (2008), ''[[Step Up 3D]]'' (2010), ''[[White Frog]]'' (2012), ''[[Revenge of the Green Dragons]]'' (2014), ''[[Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon: Sword of Destiny]]'' (2016), ''[[Crazy Rich Asians (film)|Crazy Rich Asians]]'' (2018), the [[Hulu]] web series ''[[The Legion of Extraordinary Dancers]]'' (2010\u20132011) and the [[YouTube Red]] series ''[[Single by 30]]'' (2016).\n\nShum is represented by [[Paradigm Talent Agency]], Triniti Management and Stone Genow.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/heart-of-life-harry-shum-jr-katie-findlay-cast-in-abc-drama-pilot-inspired-by-john-mayer-song-1202571531/|title=\u2018Heart Of Life\u2019: Harry Shum Jr. & Katie Findlay To Star In ABC Drama Pilot Inspired By John Mayer Song|last=Petski|first=Nellie Andreeva,Denise|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2019-03-07|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-02-03|last3=Petski|first3=Denise}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nShum was born in [[Lim\u00f3n|Lim\u00f3n, Costa Rica]], and is of ethnic [[Chinese people|Chinese]] descent. His mother is a native of [[Hong Kong]] and his father is from [[Guangzhou]], China. They relocated to Costa Rica, where Shum and his two older sisters (Cristina and Susana) were born. When Shum was six years old, the family moved to [[San Francisco]], [[California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yellowmags.com/Yellow_Nov_10.pdf|title=Nov10 1-9-P|format=PDF|accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> He stated, \"I feel I have the best of so many worlds. I speak [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Cantonese]]. Spanish is actually my first language before I learned Cantonese and [[English language|English]].\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asiancemagazine.com/2009/09/02/harry-shum-is-full-of-glee|title=Harry Shum is full of Glee|work=Asiance|last=Lin|first=Shannon|date=April 10, 2007|accessdate=July 7, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100206153253/http://asiancemagazine.com/2009/09/02/harry-shum-is-full-of-glee|archivedate=February 6, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hernandez|first=Lee|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/15-more-stars-you-never-knew-were-latino?slide=10|title=15 (More) Stars You Never Knew Were Latino!|work=[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]|accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> He later stated that he has not spoken Spanish fluently since the age of 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://daman.co.id/da-man-exclusive-harry-shum-jr/|title=Exclusive Feature: Harry Shum, Jr.|author=|date=|website=daman.co.id}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R7VqUkS7uh4|title=YouTube|author=|date=|website=www.youtube.com}}</ref>\n\nShum spent most of his schooling years in the [[San Luis Obispo County, California|San Luis Obispo area]], California and graduated from [[Arroyo Grande High School]] in 2000.<ref name=\"TribuneSLO\">{{citenews|title=A.G. High grad stars in Fox's show 'Glee'|url=http://www.sanluisobispo.com/news/local/article39143451.html|work=[[The Tribune (San Luis Obispo)]]|date=February 5, 2011}}</ref> Initially, he had been more interested in theater and sports but found a passion for dance after auditioning for his high school dance team on a dare.<ref name=\"TribuneSLO\"/><ref name=\"APAUSC2010\">{{cite web|url=http://asiapacificarts.usc.edu/article@apa?the_different_worlds_of_dance_interview_with_harry_shum_jr_16107.aspx|title=The Different Worlds of Dance: interview with Harry Shum Jr.|last=Apuy|first=Andrea|date=November 19, 2010|publisher=Asia Pacific Arts|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161126050935/http://asiapacificarts.usc.edu/article@apa?the_different_worlds_of_dance_interview_with_harry_shum_jr_16107.aspx|archive-date=November 26, 2016|accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC2017\">{{cite web|title=Harry Shum Jr. Joined a Dance Team on a Dare. These Days, He Isn\u2019t Staying Still.|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/harry-shum-jr-joined-dance-team-dare-these-days-he-n724891|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=February 27, 2017|first=Taylor|last=Weik}}</ref> Shum attended [[San Francisco State University]] for a year, before dropping out to pursue a dance career. In an interview, he said that his earliest motivations to dance were from watching [[Ginuwine]], [[Dru Hill]] and [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]], before becoming influenced by dancers like [[Gene Kelly]] and [[Michael Jackson]].<ref name=\"APAUSC2010\" />\n\nShum has stated that he identifies as being somewhat [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Latino]]. He said, \"It's strange that I am full Chinese and born in a Latin country, but I love the fact that I was immersed in that culture at birth while maintaining my Chinese roots,\" and added, \"I think the cultures share a lot of similarities as far as family values and the love for flavor in their foods. I do consider myself somewhat Latin.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mom.me/latina-mom/7602-latinos-hollywood/item/harry-shum-jr/|title=Harry Shum Jr.: Latinos in Hollywood|first=Sona|last=Charaipotra|publisher=Mom.me|date=June 3, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n=== 2002-2007: Dancer Beginnings ===\nShum began his dance career in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dancespirit.com/scene_stealer_harry_shum_jr-2326078301.html|title=Scene Stealer: Harry Shum Jr.|work=Dance Spirit|accessdate=September 24, 2011}}</ref> As a 18-year-old, he was spotted by choreographers Rosero McCoy and Jamal Sims to go on a UK tour with the singer [[Kaci Battaglia|Kaci]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dancespirit.com/scene_stealer_harry_shum_jr-2326078301.html|title=Scene Stealer: Harry Shum Jr.|date=2011-09-24|website=Dance Spirit|language=en|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> He steadily built his career, appearing as the only male dancer on [[BET]]'s ''[[ComicView|Comic View]]'',<ref name=\":0\" />  and starred in a series of [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] [[iPod]] advertisements as dancing silhouettes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2011/10/06/harry-shum-jr-ipod-commercial/|title='Glee' Star Harry Shum Jr. Starred In One Of The First iPod Ads!|last=Staff|first=Hollywood Life|date=2011-10-06|website=Hollywood Life|language=en|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2011/10/06/glee-harry-shum-jr-steve-jobs-connection/|title=Steve Jobs: How Harry Shum, Jr., was connected to the icon|website=EW.com|language=EN|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> He joined [[Beyonc\u00e9]], [[Alicia Keys]] and [[Missy Elliott]] in their co-headlining tour ''Ladies First'' in 2004,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/03/04/harry-shum-jr-what-its-like-to-have-beyonce-as-your-boss.html|title=Harry Shum Jr. explains what it's like to have Beyonce as your boss|last=Zhao|first=Helen|date=2019-03-04|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2020-02-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/harry-shum-jr-of-shadowhunters-used-to-be-a-backup-dancer-for-beyonce_n_5c82ad9de4b08d5b786160f6|title=Harry Shum Jr. Of 'Shadowhunters' Used To Be A Backup Dancer For Beyonc\u00e9|last=Yam|first=Kimberly|date=2019-03-08|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=2020-02-01}}</ref> while working as backup dancers for artists including [[Jennifer Lopez]], [[Jessica Simpson]] and [[Mariah Carey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/harry-shum-jr-joined-dance-team-dare-these-days-he-n724891|title=Harry Shum Jr. joined a dance team on a dare. These days, he isn't staying still.|website=NBC News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-01}}</ref> He appeared in several [[Music video|music videos]] of songs including [[Lose My Breath|''Lose My Breath'']] by [[Destiny's Child]] and [[It's Like That (Mariah Carey song)|''It's Like That'']] by [[Mariah Carey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2010/05/glees_harry_shum_jr_finally_sp.html|title=Glee\u2019s Harry Shum Jr. Finally Speaks (and Answers Your Questions!)|last=Milzoff|first=Rebecca|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> Shum also worked as a dance instructor.<ref>{{cite web|title=Class With Jyve Harry Shum|url=https://www.focusdancecenter.com/photo-gallery/class-with-jyve-harry-shum/|agency=FOCUS Dance Center|accessdate=2020-02-02|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== 2008-2014: Turn to Acting, ''Glee, The LXD'' ===\nSince 2008, Shum was given roles in ''[[Step Up 2: The Streets|Step Up 2]]'' and later ''[[Step Up 3D]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nymag.com/daily/entertainment/2010/05/glees_harry_shum_jr_finally_sp.html|title=Glee's Harry Shum Jr. Finally Speaks (and Answers Your Questions!)|work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|last=Milzoff|first=Rebecca|date=May 25, 2010|accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> both directed by [[Jon M. Chu]]. From 2009 until 2015, he portrayed the role of [[Mike Chang]], a dancer who joins the [[glee club]], on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] musical comedy-drama series ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uk/news/200171/asian-and-other-asian-hook-up-on-glee-is-artie-out-for-good|title=\"Asian\" and \"Other Asian\" Hook Up on Glee \u2013 Is Artie Out for Good?|publisher=[[E!|E! Online]]|last1=Mulick|first1=Marcus|last2=Arrow|first2=Jennifer|date=September 13, 2010|accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> Known for a while as \"Other Asian\" on ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'', he was given very few lines during the show's first season. Partly due to the enthusiasm from fans during his appearances on the [[Glee Live! In Concert!|live tour]] taking place after the [[Glee (season 1)|first season]] concluded, Shum's character was given storylines in the [[Glee (season 2)|second season]], mostly involving his relationship with fellow glee club member [[Tina Cohen-Chang]] ([[Jenna Ushkowitz]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/466982/harry-shum-jr-finds-his-voice-on-glee|title=Harry Shum Jr. Finds His Voice on 'Glee'|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> He subsequently gave performances of \"Make 'Em Laugh\" in \"[[The Substitute (Glee)|The Substitute]]\", \"Sing\" from ''[[A Chorus Line]]'' in \"[[Duets (Glee)|Duets]]\", \"Valerie\" in \"[[Special Education (Glee)|Special Education]]\", and the show's first dance solo in \"[[A Night of Neglect]]\". He was promoted from guest star to series regular for the third season.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.foxflash.com/div.php/main/page?aID=1z4&mo=9&d=20|title=Glee club is back in session on the season premiere of ''Glee''|publisher=[[Fox Broadcasting Company]]|accessdate=September 2, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131209031828/http://www.foxflash.com/div.php/main/page?aID=1z4&mo=9&d=20|archivedate=December 9, 2013}}</ref> He was given a major storyline in the third episode of the season, \"[[Asian F]]\", and performed \"[[Cool (Leonard Bernstein song)|Cool]]\" from ''[[West Side Story]]'', his first solo song. On June 28, 2013, it was reported that Shum would not return as regular on ''Glee''{{'s}} fifth season, but would be a recurring guest star.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2013/06/28/glee-season-5-cast-heather-morris-mark-salling-not-returning/|title=''Glee'' Exclusive: 4 Original Cast Members Not Returning as Series Regulars for Season 5|publisher=[[TVLine]]|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=June 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\nShum worked as both a choreographer and a dancer for the dance group [[The Legion of Extraordinary Dancers|The LXD]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2010/10/30/glees-harry-shum-jr-on-the-creepy-halloween-timed-rising-episode-of-the-lxd/|title=\u2018Glee\u2019s\u2019 Harry Shum Jr. on the Creepy Halloween-Timed \u2018Rising\u2019 Episode of The LXD|last=Steinberg|first=Julie|date=2010-10-31|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/09/glees-harry-shum-talks-the-situ-asian-asian-camp-and-the-lxd.html|title='Glee's' Harry Shum talks 'The Situ-Asian,' Asian Camp and The LXD \u2013 From Inside the Box|publisher=[[Zap2it.com]]|last=Nguyen|first=Hanh|accessdate=July 7, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110912003156/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/09/glees-harry-shum-talks-the-situ-asian-asian-camp-and-the-lxd.html|archive-date=September 12, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>. Along with Chrisopher Scott, Harry choreographed performances during the ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show|Ellen]]''<nowiki/>'s Even Bigger Really Big Show, the [[82nd Academy Awards]] and ''[[So You Think You Can Dance (American TV series)|So You Think You Can Dance]]''. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1484270/|title=Harry Shum Jr.|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> The LXD also worked as the opening act for the [[Glee Live! In Concert!|''Glee Live! In Concert!'']] tour starting in May 2010. A mini [[web series]] of the same name and starring the ''[[The Legion of Extraordinary Dancers|The LXD]]'' was created by [[Jon M. Chu]], with Shum again taking the position of the choreographer and portrayed Elliot, while also writing the script for one of the episodes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Harry Shum Jr.|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1484270/|agency=IMDb|accessdate=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n\nShum has been featured in many productions of [[Wong Fu Productions]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/online/oscars/2010/05/glees-harry-shum-jr-mike-would-love-to-spew-diet-soda-on-you.html|title=Glee's Harry Shum Jr. Speaks! (And He Wants His Gaga Costume)|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|last=Berk|first=Brett|date=May 18, 2010}}</ref> In 2011, Shum worked in a short action film, ''[[3 Minutes]]'', directed by [[Ross Ching]] and produced by [[Don Le]] and [[George Wang (producer)|George Wang]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pagesix.com/2011/01/10/3-minutes-for-harry-shum-to-save-the-world/|title='3 Minutes' for Harry Shum to save the world|work=[[New York Post]]|last=Wieselman|first=Jarett|date=January 10, 2011|accessdate=August 23, 2011}}</ref> In 2012 he starred in ''[[White Frog]]'', a [[Comedy-drama|comedy-drama film]] directed by [[Quentin Lee]]. Subsequently Shum was cast in the role of the [[Sub-Zero (Mortal Kombat)|Kuai Liang]] (the younger Sub-Zero) in the second season of ''[[Mortal Kombat: Legacy]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latino-review.com/news/2012/12/web-series-mortal-kombat-legacy-2-hitting-february-17th|title=Web Series 'Mortal Kombat: Legacy 2' Hitting February 17th|publisher=Latino Review|date=December 3, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305221606/http://www.latino-review.com/news/2012/12/web-series-mortal-kombat-legacy-2-hitting-february-17th|archivedate=March 5, 2016}}</ref> In 2014, he had a major role in crime drama film ''[[Revenge of the Green Dragons]]'', which was executive produced by [[Martin Scorsese]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1982283/harry-shum-jr-revenge-of-the-green-dragons/|title='Revenge Of The Green Dragons' Will Change How You See Harry Shum Jr.|last=Sullivan|first=Kevin P.|website=MTV News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-04}}</ref> Shum was also the judge on the [[reality competition]] television series ''[[Face Off (TV series)|Fake-Off]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2014/06/11/fake-off-judges/|title=Harry Shum Jr., Chilli, and Michael Curry to judge new truTV series 'Fake Off'|website=EW.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015-2018: ''Shadowhunters'', Films ===\nIn 2016, Shum appeared as the character Wei-Fang in the [[Netflix]] American\u2013Chinese [[martial arts film]] ''[[Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon: Sword of Destiny]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.movieline.com/2010/04/harry-shum-jr-on-the-perks-of-glee-oprah-and-on-set-dance-battles.php|title=Harry Shum Jr. on the Perks of Glee, Oprah and On-Set Dance Battles|publisher=[[Movieline]]|last=Miller|first=Julie|date=April 13, 2010|accessdate=July 7, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110821020858/http://www.movieline.com/2010/04/harry-shum-jr-on-the-perks-of-glee-oprah-and-on-set-dance-battles.php|archive-date=August 21, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/glees-harry-shum-jr-joins-722369C|title='Glee's' Harry Shum Jr. Joins 'Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon' Sequel|last=Jeffery|first=Morgan|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=July 30, 2014}}</ref> a sequel to ''[[Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon]]'' (1999). Shum was also cast as the male lead, Peter Ma, in [[Single by 30|''Single By 30'']], a [[YouTube Red]] original series from Wong Fu Productions and New Form Digital after starring in the original pilot in 2015. The first season of the series premiered on August 24, 2016, on Wong Fu Productions' Channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/glees-harry-shum-jr-star-888460|title=''Glee''{{'s}} Harry Shum Jr. to Star in YouTube Red Rom-Com ''Single by 30''|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nShum scored a lead role in the [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] series, ''[[Shadowhunters]]'', and portrayed the centuries-old [[warlock]] [[Magnus Bane]] between 2016 and 2019. The show is based on [[Cassandra Clare]]'s best-selling [[Young adult fiction|young adult]] [[Fantasy literature|fantasy]] series, ''[[The Mortal Instruments]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/harry-shum-jr-joining-abc-familys-shadowhunters/|title='Glee' Star Harry Shum Jr. Joining ABC Family's 'Shadowhunters'|last=Ge|first=Linda|date=May 15, 2015|publisher=[[TheWrap]]}}</ref> His portrayal of Bane, a bisexual man of color, helped ''Shadowhunters'' win the 2017 [[GLAAD]] media award for an \"Outstanding Drama Series\", which he accepted with his co-star [[Matthew Daddario]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/glaad-media-awards-2017-complete-winners-list-1202058159/|title='GLAAD Media Awards 2017 Complete Winners List'|date=October 16, 2017|publisher='deadline'}}</ref> Shum also received the [[Bisexual Representation Award]] (BiRA) for \"Best Bisexual Representation of a Supporting Character\" in both 2017 and 2018 hosted by [[FluidStyleCo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/first-bisexual-representation-award-winners-announced_us_59d40efce4b08c2a000ddcc0|title=First 'Bisexual Representation Award' Winners Announced|last=YoungMiller|first=Cristian|date=2017-10-03|website=Huffington Post|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-11}}</ref> Shum won the award for The Male TV Star of 2018 in the [[E! People's Choice Awards]] for his role as Magnus Bane in ''Shadowhunters''. \n\nAlongside his work in ''[[Shadowhunters]]'', he received supporting roles in movies including ''[[Escape Plan: The Extractors]]'' and ''[[Burn (2019 film)|Burn]]''. In 2018, Shum was cast as Charlie Wu in Jon M. Chu's [[Crazy Rich Asians (film)|''Crazy Rich Asians,'']]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/08/15/crazy-rich-asians-mid-credits-scene-harry-shum-jr-gemma-chan/|title='Crazy Rich Asians' director talks mid-credits scene \u2014 and the Harry Shum Jr. scene you didn\u2019t see|work=EW.com|access-date=2018-11-11|language=en}}</ref> and despite most of his scenes being cut due to the desire to focus on one romantic pairing, he appears briefly in a mid-credits scene near the end.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/harry-shum-jr-crazy-rich-asians-movie-cut-scenes/|title=Why Harry Shum Jr. Was Cut From Crazy Rich Asians|date=2018-08-16|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> An implied romance between Astrid and his character Charlie is to be expanded in the movie sequels currently in the work.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/film-tv/a22801111/crazy-rich-asians-sequel/|title=The 'Crazy Rich Asians' Sequel Will Feature a New Love Story|date=2018-08-22|work=Harper's BAZAAR|access-date=2018-11-11|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019-Present ===\nIn 2019 Shum appeared in 4 episodes of ''[[Tell Me a Story (TV series)|Tell Me a Story]]'' which premiered in December 2019. In late 2019, it was announced that Shum would star in ''[[All My Life (upcoming film)|All My Life]]'' alongside [[Jessica Rothe]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/harry-shum-jr-star-universals-love-story-all-my-life-1244955|title=Harry Shum Jr. to Star in Universal's Love Story 'All My Life' (Exclusive)|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> as well as the [[Thriller film|thriller]] movie ''[[Broadcast Signal Intrusion (upcoming film)|Broadcast Signal Intrusion]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/harry-shum-jr-chris-sullivan-glee-thriller-broadcast-signal-intrusion-1202763523/|title=Harry Shum Jr. & Chris Sullivan Lead Cast In Movie Thriller \u2018Broadcast Signal Intrusion\u2019|last=Wiseman|first=Andreas|last2=Wiseman|first2=Andreas|date=2019-10-18|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n\nShum was included in the [https://goldhouse.org/a100/ A100 List of 2019], a celebration of the 100 most influential public figures of [[Asian Americans|Asian]] & [[Pacific Islands Americans|Pacific Islanders]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goldhouse.org/a100/|title=A100|website=GoldHouse|language=en|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nShum began a relationship with [[Filipino-American]] dancer [[Shelby Rabara]] in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bullettmedia.com/article/glees-harry-shum-jr-on-his-worst-breakup/|title=Glee's Harry Shum Jr. on His Worst Breakup, Longest Relationship, & Dancing it Off|publisher=Bullett Media|last=Alcala|first=Natalie|date=September 24, 2012}}</ref> The two were engaged in October 2013 while on vacation in [[Hawaii]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20795239,00.html|title=Mike Chang is getting married! Glee star Harry Shum Jr. engaged to longtime love Shelby Rabara|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|last=Blumm|first=K.C.|date=March 8, 2014}}</ref> and were married on November 22, 2015 in [[Costa Rica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/glee-harry-shum-jr-marries-shelby-rabara|title=Glee Star Harry Shum Jr. Marries Shelby Rabara|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|last=Park|first=Andrea|date=December 4, 2015|accessdate=December 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC2017\"/> \n\nOn November 11, 2018, the couple announced via social media that they are expecting their first child, a baby girl.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/985933/glee-s-harry-shum-jr-expecting-first-child-with-wife-shelby-rabara|title=Glee's Harry Shum Jr. Expecting First Child With Wife Shelby|last=|first=|date=Nov 11, 2018|work=E! Online|access-date=|language=en-US}}</ref> The birth of their daughter, Xia, was announced on March 28, 2019.<ref> {{cite web|url= https://www.popsugar.com/celebrity/Harry-Shum-Jr-Shelby-Rabara-Welcome-First-Child-45971553 |title= She's Here! Harry Shum Jr. and Shelby Rabara Welcome a Baby Girl|work=[[PopSugar]]|last=Sisavat|first=Monica|date=March 28, 2019|accessdate=March 28, 2019}} </ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[You Got Served]]''\n| Dancer\n| Cameo\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Stomp the Yard]]''\n| Crew Dancer\n| Cameo\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2008\n|''[[The Onion Movie]]''\n|Lollipop love dancer\n|Cameo\n|-\n|''[[Step Up 2: The Streets]]''\n| Cable\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Center Stage: Turn It Up]]''\n| Club Dancer\n| Cameo\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2010\n| ''[[Our Family Wedding]]''\n| Harry\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Step Up 3D]]''\n| Cable\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2011\n| ''[[3 Minutes]]''\n| Hunter #1\n| Short film\n|-\n| ''[[Glee: The 3D Concert Movie]]''\n| [[Mike Chang]]\n| Concert film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2012\n| ''[[White Frog]]''\n| Chaz Young\n|\n|-\n| ''Already Gone''\n| Scott Lee\n| Short film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014\n| ''[[Moms' Night Out]]''\n| Joey\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Revenge of the Green Dragons]]''\n| Paul Wong\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Fire City: End of Days''\n| Frank\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon: Sword of Destiny]]''\n| Wei-Fang\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n|''[[Crazy Rich Asians (film)|Crazy Rich Asians]]''\n| Charlie Wu\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2019\n| ''[[Burn (2019 film)|Burn]]''\n| Officer Liu\n|\n|-\n|''[[Escape Plan: The Extractors]]''\n|Bao Yung\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n|[[Broadcast Signal Intrusion (upcoming film)|''Broadcast Signal Intrusion'']]\n|James\n|''Post-production''\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[All My Life (upcoming film)|All My Life]]''\n|Solomon Chau\n|''Post-production''\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Boston Public]]''\n| Fletcher\n| Episode: \"Chapter Sixty\"\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Committed (2005 TV series)|Committed]]''\n| Chinese Delivery Guy\n| Episode: \"The Apartment Episode\"\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Viva Laughlin]]''\n| Construction Dancer\n| Episode: \"Pilot\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2008\n| ''[[Zoey 101]]''\n| Roy\n| Episode: \"Trading Places\"\n|-\n| ''[[Rita Rocks]]''\n| Zack\n| Episode: \"Flirting with Disaster\"\n|-\n| ''[[The American Mall]]''\n| Dancing Taco\n| Television film\n|-\n| ''[[Greek (TV series)|Greek]]''\n| Omega Chi Brother\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[iCarly]]''\n| Y\u00fbki\n| Episode: \"[[iGo to Japan]]\"\n|-\n| 2009\u201315\n| ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''\n| [[Mike Chang]]\n| Recurring role (seasons 1\u20142, 5\u20146); Main role (seasons 3\u20144), 76 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The Eric Andre Show]]''\n| Himself\n| 1 episode\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Face Off (TV series)|Fake-Off]]''\n|Himself\n|Judge (seasons 1\u20142), 16 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\u201319\n| ''[[Shadowhunters]]''\n| [[Magnus Bane]]\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Heart of Life''\n| Brendan Winter\n| Unsold TV Pilot\n|-\n| 2019\u201320\n| ''[[Tell Me a Story (TV series)|Tell Me a Story]]''\n| Brendan\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Awkwafina Is Nora from Queens]]''\n| Doc Hottie\n| Episode: \"Grandma & Chill\"\n|}\n\n===Web===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 2010\u201311\n| ''[[The Legion of Extraordinary Dancers]]''\n| Elliot Hoo\n| 9 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Mortal Kombat: Legacy]]''\n| [[Sub-Zero (Mortal Kombat)#Kuai Liang|Kuai Liang]]\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Caper''\n| Luke Washington\n| 9 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Single by 30]]''\n| Peter Ma\n| 8 episodes\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Work\n! Award\n! Category\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2010\n| rowspan=\"4\"| ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''\n| [[16th Screen Actors Guild Awards|Screen Actors Guild Awards]]\n| Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Comedy Series\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[2010 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Music: Group <small>(with cast)</small>